==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Refait
<hw>Re*fait"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety>
<fld>(Card Playing)</fld> <def>A drawn game;</def>
<specif>specif.</specif> <fld>(Trente et quarante)</fld>, <def>A state
of the game in which the aggregate pip value of cards dealt to red
equals that of those dealt to black. All bets are then off; unless the
value is 31, in which case the banker wins half the stakes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Refar</ent>⟦br⟧
